rComments: Professor obviously loves teaching and is passionate about his research. Easy A if you show up to class and the textbook readings help you do even better. He only expects you to read a small portion of the book. Sad he's retiring!

Easiest prof ever... don't worry about going to class, He posts all the videos he shows and his slides are useless anyways... Read the textbook and following the assigned reading list closely and you'll get an A. 2 midterms and a final, gives bonus marks.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: A bit odd at times, but generally an incredibly kind and caring prof. The way he taught the course and followed the textbook closely made for an easy A. Bonus points on each midterm and on the exam. Great video examples of children screeching and whatnot.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Caring', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I love Prof Younger! One of my favourite professors at uOttawa by far. He clearly cares about the success of his students so his tests are super fair if you go to class, study the lectures, and do the readings ! He's also very sweet and funny. Would recommend to anyone!

Loved this class. Took is as part of my minor and Prof Younger was great. He is very passionate about what he is teaching and is knowledgeable in his field. He loves to imitate crying babies haha. Do go to class as not all the info is on the powerpoint, textbook is a good asset & two MC midterms (bonus questions on both). Would take again!

Prepare to read, but any psych student already knows that. Tests include bonus questions to take the hurt off. They were easy, though, as long as you read the book and attended class fairly regularly. AY is hilarious and is very passionate about his field. It is a shame that he is retiring.
Had Prof Younger for Child Development and it was my favourite class. He is so kind and really funny!

I loved this class. The prof involved students but doesn't force anyone to participate. His midterms and the exam had clear expectations. The TA was great too. He's super funny and you'll love his many imitations

Love him! He's such a nice guy and really slow with the material, in a good way. He's a great lecturer. Easy A+, textbook readings are useful to do but not necessary to study, he tests mostly from his lectures.
The sweetest old man I've ever met. Really inspiring and captivating. Would definitely take his classes again!

Easy A class. Just show up and fill in whatever he doesn't already have on the slides. Concepts are simple and intuitive, so studying half an hour the night before got me a 90% on the midterm. Non-cumulative tests. As a Science student taking this class as an elective, it was a joke, but perhaps because I'm used to harder. Little to no workload.

Good prof, funny and tries to keep the classes interesting by using personal stories. Exams were all multiple choice and definitions and no assignments. Enthusiastic about content and is an overall nice prof. I would recommend!

Great professor and really interested in what he is teaching, but the powerpoint slides in class are a mess.  I relied on the textbook, which he wrote, to get me through the class.  Not an easy A at all because his exams are hard, but if you really want to understand and take something away from the course I would suggest him as a professor.
Very approachable & nice. His exams are difficult-percentages, extremely nit-picky. Not an easy A. Class lectures were boring, however it was entertaining when he imitated babies.

Social Development of the Child. His exams are really nit-picky. He picks specifics, like percentages, etc on his final. That aside he is an incredible interesting lecturer, and presents cool videos. There is also a great oral presentation part to the course which is easy marks.
Such a great professor. He is the best professor I've had without a doubt. Very enthusiastic : )
great class, cute videos on kids, teaches well, but hard midterms/exams. tests on the textbook but definitions are more on lectures. a bit hard to get an A but still worth taking with him!
Not a fan of the way he composes the exams!

great guy! knows his stuff! uses a fair amount of textbook and lecture material. tests more on the outcomes and specifics of studies rather than definitions of concepts. very nice man and pretty good teacher!

An amazing Prof. So into what he teaches, he's a very good baby imitator lol! Attend his class,u'll love it,always clear and easy, you won't even feel time passing by. He's a keeper! we need more profs like him in this Uni,you need to study and know your stuff!you do need to focus but overall easy course.

Very clear and nice prof. You can tell he loves teaching and is willing to help his students. Lectures were very clear and amusing as he tells funny anecdotes that actually relate to the course. He helped write the textbook so he knows what he's talking about. Loved this class, loved this prof!

Amazing Prof. He is so nice, kind hearted, funny, helpful. Tells funny stories which help learn the material. He is always there to help, I wish he taught more classes! Fair tests, info is straight from the lectures and text. Alistair's superb.

What a great prof, with fair exams if you know your stuff. I would recommend Alistair to any student out there, as he is extremely fun and approachable. Going to class is not a hassle, and there is little to no workload to go along with the class (except for some readings). Definitely recommended.

Awesome prof. Interesting subject. Fair midterms and exam. All the elements of a good course are there. I recommend this class to the other Biomedical science students who are undecided between this course and PSY2114
Great prof- sincere, engaging, funny. Knows the material and provides good examples that are usually hilarious. Definitely recommended!

This prof is great! he usually spends half the class telling really funny stories from his own experience or about his son. :) sometimes the class goes slowly but he makes everything really really clear. just make sure you read the text book because he throws stuff on the exams from the text that he may not have covered in class.
He's hilarious. Teaches his material in a smooth and fun way, although it's a bit slow or tedious at times. He's light-hearted, funny, and very approachable.

Great guy, engaging lectures, awesome prof. Likes to tell us embarassing stories about his son. He is the only prof I've had who can make a class *with* him and not *at* him. Younger is highly recommended!

Prof. Younger is very entertaining. His anecdotes never fail to make me laugh, and he gets down right silly at times, but always in a good way.  I really enjoy going to his class, even though I was/am not particularily interested in Child Development.  He seems like a genuinely kind person.
one of the best prof's ive had, sincere and creates interest in subject
he makes a not so interesting subject very interesting. hes hilarious and cute, if you have him, youre lucky!

Very comprehensive, funny, kind, and enthusiastic. One of the best profs I've had. VERRRY good at teaching research methods.

Had his for child development - easy to follow, good overheards, great lecturer - sometimes a little slow going, but very clear.  Nice guy, good sense of humour, good inflection with his voice (ie no monotone here kids)
